Floy Clements https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Floy_Clements 0 Floy Mae Clements (née Stephens November 20, 1891 – September 29, 1973) was an African American politician in Illinois notable for being the first African American woman to serve in the Illinois General Assembly upon her election to the Illinois House of Representatives in 1958.
